SENATE BILL 544
D1 6lr2499
CF HB 492
By: Chair, Judicial Proceedings Committee (By Request – Maryland Judicial
Conference)
Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Judicial Proceedings
Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: February 20, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Courtroom Security – Minimum Adequate Security Standard
3 FOR the purpose of establishing minimum adequate security standards for courtroom
4 security at all courthouse facilities; and generally relating to courtroom security.
5 BY adding to
6 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
7 Section 1–206
8 Annotated Code of Maryland
9 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
10 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
11 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
12 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
13 1–206.
14 (A) THERE IS A MINIMUM ADEQUATE SECURITY STANDARD FOR
15 COURTROOM SECURITY AT ALL COURTHOUSE FACILITIES IN THE STATE.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0544*

2 SENATE BILL 544
1 (B) FOR THE PURPOSES OF THIS SECTION, A COURT SECURITY OFFICER
2 MUST MEET THE QUALIFICATIONS FOR A SPECIAL POLICE OFFICER AS DEFINED IN §
3 3–301 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE.
4 (C) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2027, DURING COURT PROCEEDINGS, ANY ENTITY
5 RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING COURTHOUSE SECURITY SHALL USE BEST EFFORTS
6 TO HAVE PRESENT A MINIMUM OF:
7 (1) ONE COURT SECURITY OFFICER IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
8 CRIMINAL, FAMILY, OR JUVENILE PROCEEDING;
9 (2) TWO COURT SECURITY OFFICERS IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
10 PROCEEDING INVOLVING AN INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL OR AN INDIVIDUAL WHO
11 MAY BE REMANDED TO CUSTODY AS A RESULT OF THE PROCEEDING; AND
12 (3) ONE ADDITIONAL COURT SECURITY OFFICER FOR EVERY FOUR OR
13 FEWER COURTROOMS ON EACH FLOOR OF A COURTHOUSE.
14 (D) BEGINNING JULY 1, 2029, DURING COURT PROCEEDINGS, ANY ENTITY
15 RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING COURTHOUSE SECURITY SHALL USE BEST EFFORTS
16 TO HAVE PRESENT A MINIMUM OF:
17 (1) ONE COURT SECURITY OFFICER IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
18 TYPE OF PROCEEDING;
19 (2) TWO COURT SECURITY OFFICERS IN EACH COURTROOM FOR ANY
20 PROCEEDING INVOLVING AN INCARCERATED INDIVIDUAL OR ANY INDIVIDUAL WHO
21 MAY BE REMANDED INTO CUSTODY AS A RESULT OF THE PROCEEDING; AND
22 (3) ONE ADDITIONAL COURT SECURITY OFFICER FOR EVERY FOUR OR
23 FEWER COURTROOMS ON EACH FLOOR OF A COURTHOUSE.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2026.

